        "created_at": "2018-11-16T06:20:11.921Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I am new to Foundationdb, and I had a query where I\u2019m interested to know the lifecycle of connections between the client and FDB processes (Couldn\u2019t find an answer in the documentation). Specifically, my query can be broken down into three questions as below:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>How many connections does a client open while making a connection? And connections to what?  (If any of them are different from the ones mentioned <a href=\"https://forums.foundationdb.org/t/understanding-inter-communication/745\">here</a>)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>How long are these connections open for (per transaction or per client)?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Does the client have to close the above connections or does it happen automatically?</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I would love to understand this better and any help will be appreciated. Thanks!</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 2,
        "updated_at": "2018-11-16T06:29:26.939Z",
        "reply_count": 1,
